cs.LG, cs.CE, cs.CV, cs.NE, cs.HC 

This paper involves the development of a convolutional neural network (CNN) for classification of multiple diagnoses from 12-lead electrocardiograms (ECGs). Therefore, it is likely to belong to the sub-category of Machine Learning (cs.LG) as it involves the development of a multi-task learning model. Additionally, it involves the use of clinical interpretations by cardiologists, which suggests that it may also belong to the sub-category of Clinical Informatics (cs.CE). The use of CNNs for image classification also suggests that it may belong to the sub-category of Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (cs.CV). Furthermore, the focus on ECGs and cardiac diagnoses suggests that it may belong to the sub-categories of Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) and Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC).
